<paragraph blockId="48.[151,753,1590,1616]" box="[151,753,1590,1616]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,753,1590,1616]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,753,1590,1616]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illiger" authorityYear="1807" baseAuthorityName="Lotfalizadeh et al." baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[151,272,1590,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Eurytoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonging to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1878" box="[486,577,1590,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[486,577,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1661,2010]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
The group, here considered in its restricted sense (
<bibRefCitation author="Lotfalizadeh" box="[735,1017,1661,1686]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Lotfalizadeh" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="441 - 510" refId="ref49366" refString="Lotfalizadeh, H., Delvare, G. &amp; Rasplus, J. - Y. (2007) Phylogenetic analysis of Eurytominae (Chalcidoidea: Eurytomidae) based on morphological characters. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 151, 441 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2007.00308. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Lotfalizadeh 
<emphasis box="[889,940,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), can be diagnosed as follows: gena margined posteriorly by raised carina (
<figureCitation box="[590,697,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="52.[151,264,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,205,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1419,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 22A–G. Eurytoma asphodeli. A–F, ♀. G, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in posterior view. C, same in anterolateral view. D, mesopleuron in anterolateral view. E, propodeum. F, procoxa in anterior view. G, antenna. Abbreviations. epm, epicnemium; epmc, epicnemial carina; epst2-vf, ventral shelf of mesepisternum; pgl, postgenal lamina; ppt-mvt, medioventral tooth of prepectal belt. A, B &amp; C, ex Asphodelus sp., Şirinköy village, Gökçe Ada Island, Aegean Sea, Turkey. D, on collected on spike of A. cerasiferus, Lapanouse-de-Cernon, Aveyron, France. E &amp; G, ex A. albus delphinensis from Vielha, Lleida, Spain. F, ex A. cerasiferus, Aitona, Lleida, Spain." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2667996/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 22C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[710,762,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,209,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 25A–G. A–E, Eurytoma genale. A–D, ♀; E, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in lateral view. C, antenna. D, pro- and mesonotum. E, antenna. F–G. Eurytoma pistaciae Rondani, ♀. F, antenna. G, hind leg and metasoma. All specimens from Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy; E. genale ex A. lutea, E. pistaciae from A. ramosus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668002/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">25D</figureCitation>
); back of head with raised postgenal lamina visible even in lateral view and with ventral postgenal depression (
<figureCitation box="[731,835,1733,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="52.[151,264,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,205,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1419,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 22A–G. Eurytoma asphodeli. A–F, ♀. G, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in posterior view. C, same in anterolateral view. D, mesopleuron in anterolateral view. E, propodeum. F, procoxa in anterior view. G, antenna. Abbreviations. epm, epicnemium; epmc, epicnemial carina; epst2-vf, ventral shelf of mesepisternum; pgl, postgenal lamina; ppt-mvt, medioventral tooth of prepectal belt. A, B &amp; C, ex Asphodelus sp., Şirinköy village, Gökçe Ada Island, Aegean Sea, Turkey. D, on collected on spike of A. cerasiferus, Lapanouse-de-Cernon, Aveyron, France. E &amp; G, ex A. albus delphinensis from Vielha, Lleida, Spain. F, ex A. cerasiferus, Aitona, Lleida, Spain." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2667996/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 22C</figureCitation>
); lower face with radiating carinae reaching up to the antennal toruli, interantennal space not projecting (
<figureCitation box="[737,847,1769,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="52.[151,264,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,205,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1419,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 22A–G. Eurytoma asphodeli. A–F, ♀. G, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in posterior view. C, same in anterolateral view. D, mesopleuron in anterolateral view. E, propodeum. F, procoxa in anterior view. G, antenna. Abbreviations. epm, epicnemium; epmc, epicnemial carina; epst2-vf, ventral shelf of mesepisternum; pgl, postgenal lamina; ppt-mvt, medioventral tooth of prepectal belt. A, B &amp; C, ex Asphodelus sp., Şirinköy village, Gökçe Ada Island, Aegean Sea, Turkey. D, on collected on spike of A. cerasiferus, Lapanouse-de-Cernon, Aveyron, France. E &amp; G, ex A. albus delphinensis from Vielha, Lleida, Spain. F, ex A. cerasiferus, Aitona, Lleida, Spain." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2667996/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 22A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[861,912,1769,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,209,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 25A–G. A–E, Eurytoma genale. A–D, ♀; E, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in lateral view. C, antenna. D, pro- and mesonotum. E, antenna. F–G. Eurytoma pistaciae Rondani, ♀. F, antenna. G, hind leg and metasoma. All specimens from Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy; E. genale ex A. lutea, E. pistaciae from A. ramosus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668002/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">25A</figureCitation>
), ventral belt of prepectus with sharp median tooth (
<figureCitation box="[232,349,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="52.[151,264,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,205,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1419,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 22A–G. Eurytoma asphodeli. A–F, ♀. G, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in posterior view. C, same in anterolateral view. D, mesopleuron in anterolateral view. E, propodeum. F, procoxa in anterior view. G, antenna. Abbreviations. epm, epicnemium; epmc, epicnemial carina; epst2-vf, ventral shelf of mesepisternum; pgl, postgenal lamina; ppt-mvt, medioventral tooth of prepectal belt. A, B &amp; C, ex Asphodelus sp., Şirinköy village, Gökçe Ada Island, Aegean Sea, Turkey. D, on collected on spike of A. cerasiferus, Lapanouse-de-Cernon, Aveyron, France. E &amp; G, ex A. albus delphinensis from Vielha, Lleida, Spain. F, ex A. cerasiferus, Aitona, Lleida, Spain." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2667996/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 22D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[370,402,1806,1830]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1393,717,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,697,1876]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 24. Eurytoma genale Askew &amp; Stojanova sp. n., ♀ ex Asphodeline lutea, Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668000/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">24</figureCitation>
); mesepisternum with completely delimited epicnemium and ventral shelf (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1423,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1393,717,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,697,1876]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 24. Eurytoma genale Askew &amp; Stojanova sp. n., ♀ ex Asphodeline lutea, Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668000/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); propodeum with wide mesal depression with irregular sculpture (
<figureCitation box="[900,1004,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="52.[151,264,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,205,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1419,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 22A–G. Eurytoma asphodeli. A–F, ♀. G, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in posterior view. C, same in anterolateral view. D, mesopleuron in anterolateral view. E, propodeum. F, procoxa in anterior view. G, antenna. Abbreviations. epm, epicnemium; epmc, epicnemial carina; epst2-vf, ventral shelf of mesepisternum; pgl, postgenal lamina; ppt-mvt, medioventral tooth of prepectal belt. A, B &amp; C, ex Asphodelus sp., Şirinköy village, Gökçe Ada Island, Aegean Sea, Turkey. D, on collected on spike of A. cerasiferus, Lapanouse-de-Cernon, Aveyron, France. E &amp; G, ex A. albus delphinensis from Vielha, Lleida, Spain. F, ex A. cerasiferus, Aitona, Lleida, Spain." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2667996/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 22E</figureCitation>
); procoxa with oblique depression on anterior side not delimited laterally by carina (
<figureCitation box="[676,777,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="52.[151,264,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,205,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1419,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURES 22A–G. Eurytoma asphodeli. A–F, ♀. G, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in posterior view. C, same in anterolateral view. D, mesopleuron in anterolateral view. E, propodeum. F, procoxa in anterior view. G, antenna. Abbreviations. epm, epicnemium; epmc, epicnemial carina; epst2-vf, ventral shelf of mesepisternum; pgl, postgenal lamina; ppt-mvt, medioventral tooth of prepectal belt. A, B &amp; C, ex Asphodelus sp., Şirinköy village, Gökçe Ada Island, Aegean Sea, Turkey. D, on collected on spike of A. cerasiferus, Lapanouse-de-Cernon, Aveyron, France. E &amp; G, ex A. albus delphinensis from Vielha, Lleida, Spain. F, ex A. cerasiferus, Aitona, Lleida, Spain." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2667996/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 22F</figureCitation>
); metacoxa basidorsally bare (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1205,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1393,717,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,697,1876]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 24. Eurytoma genale Askew &amp; Stojanova sp. n., ♀ ex Asphodeline lutea, Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668000/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); gaster subpetiolate with petiole bearing two small anterolateral teeth and a mediodorsal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[992,1076,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1393,717,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[151,1436,697,1876]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 24. Eurytoma genale Askew &amp; Stojanova sp. n., ♀ ex Asphodeline lutea, Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668000/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1661,2010]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
The pair of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illiger" authorityYear="1807" baseAuthorityName="Lotfalizadeh et al." baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[351,461,1950,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[351,461,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Eurytoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species associated with asphodels may be separated from the remaining species belonging to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1878" box="[348,432,1985,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[348,432,1985,2010]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group especially by the aspect of the notauli. The group may be split in two sets, also according to the habitus of the notauli. In the first set, to which belongs 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1876" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" box="[969,1304,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigifrons">
<emphasis box="[969,1117,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">E. strigifrons</emphasis>
Thomson, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, the notauli are narrow but distinctly impressed with a smooth bottom and step-like margins; in the second set, which especially includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Mayr, 1878" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1878" box="[251,501,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[251,366,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">E. robusta</emphasis>
Mayr, 1878
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Domenichini, 2002" authorityName="Domenichini" authorityYear="2002" box="[554,879,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inulae">
<emphasis box="[554,654,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">E. inulae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Domenichini" box="[661,879,223,248]" firstAuthor="Domenichini" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="306 - 315" refId="ref48427" refString="Domenichini, G. (2002) Species of genus Eurytoma (Hym. Chalcidoidea) in Mediterranean olive grove. Bollettino di Zoologia Agraria e di Bachicoltura, 34 (3), 306 - 315." type="journal article" year="2002">Domenichini, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the notauli are conversely shallow, obliterated by the sculpture of the mesonotum, and with poorly defined lateral margins. In the two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illiger" authorityYear="1807" baseAuthorityName="Lotfalizadeh et al." baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[1140,1250,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1250,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Eurytoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
associated with asphodels, the notauli show another state: they are also well impressed but partly obliterated by the sculpture of the mesonotum and with blunt lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[639,744,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,209,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 25A–G. A–E, Eurytoma genale. A–D, ♀; E, ♂. A, head in frontal view. B, same in lateral view. C, antenna. D, pro- and mesonotum. E, antenna. F–G. Eurytoma pistaciae Rondani, ♀. F, antenna. G, hind leg and metasoma. All specimens from Vizzini, Monte Iblei, Sicilia, Italy; E. genale ex A. lutea, E. pistaciae from A. ramosus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2668002/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
